  "bridge_note": "Content-address every retrieved official source with content_sha256 and identify each fact by a durable page/table/note/XBRL source_fact_anchor. Use the canonical accounting_basis label generated by accounting_basis_id. source_fact_value_text must be the direct numeric token copied from the cited official fact after applying the separately declared unit/scale; narrative, a dash, or an analyst assumption is unknown, never zero. Rounded precision must equal the decimal place displayed by that numeric token, while an official exact structured fact uses basis=exact and increment=0. If attributable net income is not directly reported, set attribution_method to derived_from_reported_bridge and add pretax_income, income_tax_expense, consolidated_net_income, and noncontrolling_interest_net_income observations on identical statutory bases. Each zero also requires zero_value_basis=explicit_official_zero_or_reported_rounding. Reconciliation tolerance is mechanically recomputed from the source-bound precision; analysts never supply it. Repeat the canonical observations for every distinct fiscal period."
